reviewText:
My absolute favorite game of all time. <3

Where to begin. Hmm.

//Story
I think the story is probably the most important aspect of a Final Fantasy game. The story in FF8 is, well, weird. It starts off simple enough, you are a student in a military school on your way to your first assignment. After a while things become very weird, almost dreamlike, introducing characters from different timelines and so on. This is probably one of the cons for many people, because the story doesn't really make sense. But if you read into some of the theories circulating the web (*cough* Squall Is Dead *cough*), the story starts to make sense and in my opinion becomes much more enjoyanble!

//Characters
This game has a list of lovely characters. Well, some might think the main protagonist is a bit Emo and not fit as a party-leader. And that's the beauty of it, he ISN'T fit as a party leader, he doesn't even WANT to be that, he sort of was just put in that situation and has to deal with his social anxiety and peoples problems that he can't even get his head around. In my opinion that makes this game so beautiful, because Squall reminds me of me and my personal struggles I've had. Squall seems very hounest and almost autistic in his behaviour, that makes him very real and not so much a cliché hero" character.

//Gameplay
Well

